Decent enough B movie for one of those cold and rainy November Saturday afternoons. Typically predictable, slow moving, good versus evil, dragon plot. Good for some mindless entertainment. Not a lot of thought went into the plot so don't worry about having to look for some underlying story line. Not to be a spoiler, but there is none. At least this film was not made in the back of an old dark warehouse.

Special effects on the dragons was OK (I've seen better).  The script was VERY poorly written and the acting like cardboard.  A five year old will think it is a great movie, but any reasonable adult will laugh at this.

A very low budget movie in which the makers did things such as use an obviously very small number of people to try to make crowds.  The "crowd" scene at King Arthur's funeral is a cross between laughable and pitiful.  Of course according to the Arthur cannons, Arthur had no funeral.  This movie uses names such as Arthur, Guinevere, Lancelot, Merlin, Morgan le Fay, etc. the way old westerns used Jessie James, Wyatt Earp, Buffalo Bill, etc.  That is there is little relationship to actual history or legend.  All of this could have been forgivable if the movie was entertaining.  Alas it is not.

Ok, so it's a pretty low budge fastest flick that is pendant best enjoyed when you're not in the mood for something that requires a lot of thought. The acting is mostly horrible, and the story really didn't make much sense, but it's a not-to-deep fantasy that asks you to only look at the primary colors. Arthurian enthusiasts will probably find it angering, but for those looking for a relaxing fantasy with very general themes it's not too bad. The woman playing Morgan le fey has an interesting accent and really tries to be someone, as a result, her interplay with a very limp Merlin is entirely one sided. It's a bit like if someone's parents decided to pretend to be Guinevere and Lancelot and somehow got funding for a movie. For stars because it's exactly what it tries to be.

This movie took me away!
  It begins with old King Arthur on his deathbed in Camelot. Guinevere and her son, Galahad, must contend with Arthur's evil sorceress sister, Morgan, who with the help of three dragons intends to take over control of Camelot. Galahad and the last of the remaining knights must go out and find Lancelot, who's been in exile... and then must return to defend Camelot...
  If you're a fan of the legend of Camelot, and dreamy escapes, and AWESOME B movies, then this one is for you. It has an original script and likeable characters, and I found it very entertaining!

Worse porn ever! It had all the hallmarks of a great porn: terrible costumes, horrendous dialog, super low budget effects....zero action!!! Tons of innuendo, every time there was an opening for action there just was nothing. Now that being said...the death scenes were awesome!!! The dragons being blown up were perfection. This is the best movie ever and my new favorite, but I stand by what I said originally, this is by far the worse porn Ive ever seen.

Once upon a time, a high school drama teacher told his students to make a movie about Camelot. One of the class raised his hand and said they might need some adults in the movie. The teacher informed him that was what the janitorial staff was for. The result was a grade "D" movie. Don't waste your time on this thing - it makes a SyFy movie look like a major Hollywood production.
